      • constructFromBinStrRowWise

        public static UByteMatrix constructFromBinStrRowWise(int row,
                                                     int col,
                                                     java.lang.String binStr)
        Returns a new object with the given size (row X col), initialized with the given string of binary digits row-wise. Every cell of the matrix is filled with 8 binary digits. The size of the bare string should be (row * col * 8). If it's bigger, then it will be truncated from the right, and if it's smaller, then it will be right-padded with 0's. The string might be formatted with underscores or spaces as separator for readability.
        Parameters:
        row - the given row
        col - the given column
        binStr - the given string of binary digits
        Returns:
        a new object

                                                     int col,

        Returns a new object with the given size row X col, initialized with the given string of hex digits column-wise. Every cell of the matrix is filled with 2 hex digits. The size of the bare string should be (row * col * 2). If it's bigger, then it will be truncated from the right, and if it's smaller, then it will be right-padded with 0's. The string might be formatted with underscore or space as separator for readability.
